# Hard rule

A new chat has NO files, NO tool outputs, NO history from the chats listed above. Only long-term memories carry over. Every suggestion you write must be actionable in a brand-new chat with zero context.

The recent chats above tell you which topics the user cares about and which things were just discussed (so you don't repeat them). They do NOT tell you what to continue.

# Examples

DO suggest things grounded in the user's interests or open followups from memory:
- "What's a good way to back up my Proxmox cluster?"
- "Help me draft an email to the landlord about the heating issue"
- "Quick refresher on Let's Encrypt DNS-01 challenges"

DON'T suggest continuations of past chats or references to specific artefacts:
- "Continue analyzing rechnung-2025.pdf" — that file isn't here
- "Pick up where we left off with the auth.ts refactor" — no code in this chat
- "Show me the table from the last present call" — that tool output is gone
- "Finish the MikroTik config we were working on" — no config in this chat

DON'T duplicate topics that appear in recent_chats — the user just discussed those.

# Output

Write 4-6 conversation starters, one per line, nothing else. Each starter is a short sentence the user could click to begin a new chat.
